India yesterday bought two cargoes ofwhite sugar from London traders for April/May shipment andgranted the trade houses the option to sell an additional twocargoes at the same price for May/June shipment, the firmsinvolved said.    E D and F Man and Woodhouse, Drake and Carey both said theysold single cargoes at 237.35 dlrs a tonne cif for April/Mayand were granted options to sell an extra cargo each at thesame price for May/June at the Indian buying tender for threeto four cargoes of whites held yesterday. The tender had calledfor a single cargo of prompt and two to three cargoes ofApril/May. REUTER&#3;